---
// Banner above the Scalar reference, warning that "Try it" stores the API key
// in browser memory for the session. Standard practice for Stripe/Resend/etc.
---

<aside class="try-it-notice" role="note">
  <strong>Heads up:</strong> Pasting an API key into the &ldquo;Try it&rdquo; console
  stores it in your browser&rsquo;s memory for this session. Use a development
  key for browser-based experimentation rather than a production key.
</aside>

<style>
  .try-it-notice {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid #f59e0b;
    background-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
  }
  .try-it-notice strong {
    color: #fbbf24;
  }
</style>
